headline: AMD forecasts sequential revenue decline, shares fall
summary: Advanced Micro Devices on Tuesday forecast a slight decline in first-quarter revenue despite an unexpected boost from sales of its AI chips to China, raising doubt about whether it has the supply-chain clout to challenge Nvidia in ​the booming AI market.  AMD said its forecast for the current quarter also includes approximately $100 million in sales of its MI308 ‌AI chips to China, after the company had excluded it from sales forecasts for the fourth quarter in November.  Shares fell more than 5% in extended trading, after investors tried ‌to dissect how the company performed without the sales to China.
